Sentencas: Porous YSZ-Cu alloy cermet structures are prepared by sintering above the metal melting point in reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Cu-YSZ cermet solid oxide fuel cell anode prepared by high-temperature sintering

Sentencas: Unexpectedly good wetting of the molten metal within the YSZ network is obtained, resulting in cermets with fine structure and excellent electronic conductivity.
Titulo: Cu-YSZ cermet solid oxide fuel cell anode prepared by high-temperature sintering

Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells are prepared with YSZ-Cu alloy cermet as the anode.
Titulo: Cu-YSZ cermet solid oxide fuel cell anode prepared by high-temperature sintering

Sentencas: Addition of infiltrated ceria catalyst improved the initial performance.
Titulo: Cu-YSZ cermet solid oxide fuel cell anode prepared by high-temperature sintering

Sentencas: Maximum power density of about 275 mA cm(-2) and operation for about 110 h was achieved in the 700-800 degrees C range.
Titulo: Cu-YSZ cermet solid oxide fuel cell anode prepared by high-temperature sintering

Sentencas: After operation, AC impedance revealed that the high-frequency impedance was unchanged, whereas the low-frequency impedance increased.
Titulo: Cu-YSZ cermet solid oxide fuel cell anode prepared by high-temperature sintering

Sentencas: It was concluded that the Cu alloy network conductivity remains high, but catalyst stability needs improvement.
Titulo: Cu-YSZ cermet solid oxide fuel cell anode prepared by high-temperature sintering
